  "event_preview": "Watkins Glen International is a 2.454 mile (3.949 km) 11-turn permanent road course in Schuyler County, New York. The Bully Hill Vineyards 176 at The Glen is the eighth race of the 2026 NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series season and the eighth time the series has raced at the circuit since the race was introduced in 1996, removed in 2000, reinstated in 2021, dropped again in 2022, and returned from 2025. The race runs 72 laps (176.4 miles) with stage breaks at laps 20 and 45. With 38 entries for 36 positions, two teams will miss the race - the largest Truck Series entry list the circuit has seen in the modern era. This is the first time the series has used this Goodyear tyre code at Watkins Glen.\n\nFive full-time Cup Series regulars are in the field - Shane van Gisbergen in the No. 4 Niece Motorsports Chevrolet, AJ Allmendinger in the No. 25 Kaulig Racing Ram, Ross Chastain in the No. 45 Niece Motorsports Chevrolet, Connor Zilisch taking over the No. 71 Spire entry in place of Daniel Suárez, and Carson Hocevar in the No. 77 Spire Motorsports Chevrolet - Hocevar fresh off his first career Cup victory at Talladega. Toni Breidinger joins in the No. 20 McAnally-Hilgemann Chevrolet, a new development entry making its series debut this weekend. The race winner has started on the front row in six of the seven previous Truck Series events at this circuit.\n\nThe all-time Truck Series qualifying record at Watkins Glen belongs to Corey Heim, who turned a 70.953-second lap at 124.308 mph to claim pole for the 2025 Mission 176 at The Glen.",
